    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#1B2A4A] mt-8 mb-4">5.5 Why Modular Monolith, Not Microservices</h3>

    <p class="mb-4 text-[#2D2D2D] leading-relaxed">
      The RFP specifies microservices architecture. We suggest a <strong>modular monolith</strong>
      instead. This is a single deployable application with clearly separated internal modules (auth,
      graph, catalogue, export, sync) that communicate through well-defined interfaces.
    </p>

    <p class="mb-4 text-[#2D2D2D] leading-relaxed">
      <strong>Why microservices don&rsquo;t fit this project:</strong>
    </p>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
      <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse">
        <thead class="bg-[#1B2A4A] text-white">
          <tr>
            <th class="px-3 py-2 text-left font-medium">Factor</th>
            <th class="px-3 py-2 text-left font-medium">Microservices Assumption</th>
            <th class="px-3 py-2 text-left font-medium">This Project&rsquo;s Reality</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="bg-white">
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2"><strong>Data model</strong></td>
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2">Services own their own data, communicate via APIs</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2">All modules share one PostgreSQL database and the same tables</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50">
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2"><strong>Deployment cadence</strong></td>
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2">Services release independently</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2">All modules release together &mdash; there is no scenario where the graph service updates without the catalogue</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-white">
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2"><strong>Scale</strong></td>
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2">Different services need different scaling</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2">3&ndash;10 concurrent users per client, uniform load across all functions</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50">
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2"><strong>Technology diversity</strong></td>
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2">Different services need different languages or runtimes</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2">Everything is TypeScript on Node.js</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <p class="mb-4 text-[#2D2D2D] leading-relaxed">
      <strong>The cost of microservices for this project:</strong>
    </p>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
      <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse">
        <thead class="bg-[#1B2A4A] text-white">
          <tr>
            <th class="px-3 py-2 text-left font-medium">Overhead</th>
            <th class="px-3 py-2 text-left font-medium">What It Costs</th>
            <th class="px-3 py-2 text-left font-medium">Benefit at Current Scale</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="bg-white">
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2"><strong>Service-to-service communication</strong></td>
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2">Network latency on every internal call, serialisation/deserialisation, error handling for network failures</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2">None &mdash; a function call within a monolith is instant and reliable</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50">
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2"><strong>API contract management</strong></td>
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2">Each service boundary needs versioned API contracts, backward compatibility, integration testing between services</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2">None &mdash; internal module interfaces are enforced by the TypeScript compiler</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-white">
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2"><strong>Distributed tracing</strong></td>
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2">Correlating a single user request across 3&ndash;4 services requires distributed tracing infrastructure</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2">None &mdash; a single application log shows the full request path</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50">
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2"><strong>Multiple CI/CD pipelines</strong></td>
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2">Each service needs its own build, test, containerise, and deploy pipeline</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2">None &mdash; one pipeline handles everything</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-white">
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2"><strong>Infrastructure per service</strong></td>
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2">Each microservice runs in its own App Service instance (~$20/month each). 4&ndash;5 services = $80&ndash;100/month per client vs $20/month for a monolith</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2">None &mdash; adds ~$60&ndash;80/month per client with no functional benefit</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50">
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2"><strong>Operational complexity</strong></td>
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2">More containers to monitor, more failure modes, more complex debugging</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2">Negative &mdash; makes a 2-person team&rsquo;s operational burden significantly harder</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <p class="mb-4 text-[#2D2D2D] leading-relaxed">
      <strong>Estimated cost impact:</strong>
    </p>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
      <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse">
        <thead class="bg-[#1B2A4A] text-white">
          <tr>
            <th class="px-3 py-2 text-left font-medium">Item</th>
            <th class="px-3 py-2 text-left font-medium">Modular Monolith</th>
            <th class="px-3 py-2 text-left font-medium">Microservices</th>
            <th class="px-3 py-2 text-left font-medium">Difference</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="bg-white">
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2"><strong>Additional MVP development</strong></td>
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2">$0</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2">+$11,200&ndash;$16,800 (8&ndash;12 days)</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2">+$11,200&ndash;$16,800</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50">
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2"><strong>Infrastructure per client</strong></td>
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2">~$20/month (1 App Service)</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2">~$80&ndash;100/month (4&ndash;5 App Services + API gateway)</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2">+$60&ndash;80/month per client</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-white">
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2"><strong>Operational complexity</strong></td>
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2">Low (1 application, 1 pipeline, 1 log stream)</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2">High (4&ndash;5 services, 4&ndash;5 pipelines, distributed logs)</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-200 px-3 py-2">Significantly more support effort</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <p class="mb-4 text-[#2D2D2D] leading-relaxed">
      <strong>When microservices would become appropriate:</strong>
    </p>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-2 text-[#2D2D2D]">
      <li>Cloud9 grows a dedicated development team (3+ developers working on the tool full-time)</li>
      <li>A specific module has materially different scaling requirements</li>
      <li>The MLP or Matured Product phases introduce genuinely independent concerns (e.g. an AI service with different compute requirements)</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="mb-4 text-[#2D2D2D] leading-relaxed">
      At that point, the modular monolith architecture makes the extraction straightforward because
      the boundaries are already defined.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
